  "prompt": "How long do spices last before going bad?",
  "response": "The shelf life of spices varies depending on the type and how they are stored. Here's a general guide:\n\nGround Spices:\n- 2-3 years if stored properly in a cool, dark place\n- Lose potency faster than whole spices\n\nWhole Spices:\n- 3-4 years when stored correctly\n- Retain flavor and potency longer than ground spices\n\nDried Herbs:\n- 1-3 years before losing flavor\n\nStorage Tips:\n- Keep in airtight containers\n- Store away from heat and direct sunlight\n- Avoid storing near the stove\n- Keep away from moisture\n\nSigns of Spoilage:\n- Dull or faded color\n- Weak or no aroma\n- Clumping or moisture\n- Unusual smell\n\nTo maximize shelf life:\n- Buy in smaller quantities\n- Grind whole spices as needed\n- Buy from stores with high turnover\n- Date containers when purchased\n\nNote: Spices don't typically \"go bad\" in a way that makes them unsafe, but they lose flavor and potency over time.",
